WEBVTT



00:00:00.768 --> 00:00:04.576
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:00:04.384 --> 00:00:09.824
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization.

00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:18.784
using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:00:18.848 --> 00:00:27.040
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:00:27.008 --> 00:00:36.448
Today, we invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the Gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:00:38.976 --> 00:00:46.944
Peace be with you. Friends, we come to this 17th Sunday in Ordinary Time, and we have a great privilege because we're reading in our Gospel Luke's account today.

00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:49.152
Jesus' great prayer.

00:00:49.440 --> 00:00:54.816
So the disciples say, "Lord, teach us how to pray." And so Jesus himself

00:00:55.136 --> 00:01:04.256
It tells them how to pray. So it's a very sacred moment. And I think we should move into that space where Rant is asking a guru or asking someone that we admire or ask.

00:01:04.064 --> 00:01:05.952
They're asking the Son of God,

00:01:06.176 --> 00:01:16.224
How do I pray? And, you know, we become so familiar with the Our Father that I think we forget the spiritual power of it. So what I want to do is just kind of walk.

00:01:15.744 --> 00:01:22.336
walk through. And each of the evangelists has a somewhat different take, and Luke's got a few examples.

00:01:22.272 --> 00:01:24.416
distinctive features.

00:01:24.448 --> 00:01:28.672
But here's how it begins. Jesus says, "When you pray, say,

00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:29.664
Father,

00:01:29.632 --> 00:01:31.456
Hallowed be your name.

00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:36.736
So first of all, and again, I know we pray this prayer all the time, and so it just kind of runs through our mind.

00:01:36.928 --> 00:01:40.128
But pause at that opening word.

00:01:40.384 --> 00:01:41.536
Father.

00:01:42.176 --> 00:01:50.688
God is power, yes. God is the first cause of all things, yes. God is the sovereign master of the universe, yes. All that's true.

00:01:51.520 --> 00:01:57.088
But Jesus says now, when you pray, when you invoke God, you don't begin with those titles.

00:01:57.824 --> 00:01:59.200
You begin with this.

00:01:59.040 --> 00:02:01.056
Very intimate title

00:02:01.568 --> 00:02:02.688
Father.

00:02:03.424 --> 00:02:06.048
Think of that relationship with your father, right?

00:02:06.368 --> 00:02:08.288
The intimacy.

00:02:08.768 --> 00:02:10.944
That's implied.

00:02:10.944 --> 00:02:12.864
The tenderness of it.

00:02:13.440 --> 00:02:15.552
That's how we approach

00:02:15.360 --> 00:02:18.048
The creator of the entire cosmos.

00:02:18.464 --> 00:02:23.168
When you pray the Our Father next time, let that sink in. Pause.

00:02:23.328 --> 00:02:27.296
At that opening word, "Father, Father."

00:02:27.328 --> 00:02:30.240
But no, I'm going to press a little bit, even beyond this point.

00:02:30.464 --> 00:02:33.536
Because precisely as Christians,

00:02:33.632 --> 00:02:36.224
Another dimension opens up here.

00:02:37.120 --> 00:02:39.904
Jesus is in the unique sense

00:02:39.872 --> 00:02:41.632
The son of the father.

00:02:41.856 --> 00:02:45.824
right from all eternity he's the son within the life of the Trinity

00:02:47.936 --> 00:02:49.344
What's he doing now?

00:02:49.664 --> 00:02:54.144
And he's inviting us, listen now, as the Son of God, right?

00:02:54.880 --> 00:02:59.968
The one who really alone is justified in referring to the Father.

00:03:00.128 --> 00:03:02.304
But he's inviting us.

00:03:02.944 --> 00:03:06.752
To share in that relationship that he has with his father.

00:03:06.688 --> 00:03:16.608
So we're not simply signaling, as important as that is, our sort of tender childlike relationship to God. Something even more,

00:03:17.152 --> 00:03:18.816
We're praying

00:03:18.592 --> 00:03:21.344
In union with the sun

00:03:21.824 --> 00:03:27.616
We become sons and daughters in the sun. When we pray,

00:03:27.424 --> 00:03:34.784
We're not outside of God so much petitioning. We're invited by Jesus inside.

00:03:34.560 --> 00:03:37.536
inside the very life of the Trinity.

00:03:37.792 --> 00:03:39.872
think about that everybody.

00:03:39.904 --> 00:03:41.504
Next time you say,

00:03:41.696 --> 00:03:43.360
Our father

00:03:43.552 --> 00:03:47.904
It's our in the sense of all of us, but even more powerfully,

00:03:47.552 --> 00:03:49.888
I'm saying it with Jesus.

00:03:50.560 --> 00:03:53.856
He's the son, yes, in that unique sense.

00:03:54.272 --> 00:03:57.408
But we're sons and daughters in the sun.

00:03:57.856 --> 00:04:00.448
And in that relationship, we pray.

00:04:00.832 --> 00:04:02.528
And then what's the first thing?

00:04:02.208 --> 00:04:03.488
We ask.

00:04:04.256 --> 00:04:06.080
"Hell" will be your name.

00:04:05.824 --> 00:04:11.328
I know it sounds peculiar to the modern English ear. I mean, what it means is, you know,

00:04:11.296 --> 00:04:15.136
May your name be held holy.

00:04:15.648 --> 00:04:20.128
And you say, well, okay, isn't God's name always holy? Well, yeah, it is in itself, right?

00:04:20.384 --> 00:04:23.808
The prayer is, "May we

00:04:24.512 --> 00:04:29.088
Hold this name holy. Now, what does holy mean in the Bible?

00:04:28.864 --> 00:04:30.656
Kaddosh in the Hebrew.

00:04:30.400 --> 00:04:32.224
Has the sense of

00:04:32.384 --> 00:04:33.312
Other.

00:04:33.792 --> 00:04:34.720
Of

00:04:34.656 --> 00:04:36.864
Set apart.

00:04:36.960 --> 00:04:40.960
as distinctive. That's what holy means.

00:04:41.344 --> 00:04:42.720
So, Father,

00:04:42.688 --> 00:04:46.144
May we hold your name as

00:04:46.272 --> 00:04:48.512
set apart. Now, what does that mean?

00:04:48.768 --> 00:04:50.112
It means

00:04:50.336 --> 00:04:51.808
God

00:04:51.840 --> 00:04:55.040
Is without competition.

00:04:55.456 --> 00:04:57.120
The highest good

00:04:57.952 --> 00:05:05.312
so there's all the goods in the world that we seek. you know i talk about all the time pleasure and fame and power and honor and all this.

00:05:05.696 --> 00:05:07.392
Good things and we seek them

00:05:08.768 --> 00:05:14.752
But above them all, in an absolutely unique and qualitatively different sense.

00:05:15.840 --> 00:05:17.568
is the goodness of God.

00:05:18.912 --> 00:05:25.024
Deuteronomy chapter 6, the Shema prayer. Hear, O Israel, the Lord your God is God alone.

00:05:25.376 --> 00:05:26.944
No competition.

00:05:27.136 --> 00:05:32.576
Remember in the accounts of the Ten Commandments, I, the Lord your God, am a jealous God.

00:05:32.384 --> 00:05:40.064
It doesn't mean God's having emotional problems. It means he's distinctive, Kaddosh, set apart, holy, holy.

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:41.312
Hallowed.

00:05:42.304 --> 00:05:52.352
It's a very powerful scene. It's the opening move of the prayer is if we get this wrong, see, everything else will be wrong. If God is one good among many or God's like, he's number one.

00:05:51.872 --> 00:05:54.432
He's number four on my list of priorities. Right.

00:05:54.400 --> 00:05:56.928
Ah, the whole spiritual life's off kilter.

00:05:58.240 --> 00:06:03.968
"Hallowed be your name, you're the highest good, you are the summum bonum."

00:06:04.416 --> 00:06:07.168
It's a very important move in the spiritual order.

00:06:08.864 --> 00:06:10.208
Then we pray what?

00:06:10.560 --> 00:06:12.416
Your kingdom come.

00:06:12.832 --> 00:06:14.720
And your will be done,

00:06:14.656 --> 00:06:16.512
on earth as in heaven.

00:06:16.960 --> 00:06:27.008
I've said before to you, I think, that in many ways, this is the whole of the Christian spiritual life. So to get this right, and that's why Jesus places right at the heart of the

00:06:26.528 --> 00:06:27.616
of the prayer.

00:06:27.776 --> 00:06:29.920
So your kingdom come.

00:06:30.432 --> 00:06:32.576
Jesus preaching.

00:06:32.736 --> 00:06:35.360
It's is ordered to this idea, isn't it?

00:06:35.424 --> 00:06:42.592
That's what's on his lips when he begins preaching in the hills of Galilee is the kingdom of God is at hand.

00:06:44.032 --> 00:06:49.088
Every move he makes is meant to embody and express the kingdom.

00:06:50.272 --> 00:06:51.904
1. What's the kingdom? 2

00:06:52.096 --> 00:06:56.064
It's God's way of ordering things.

00:06:57.408 --> 00:07:02.176
God's way of ordering things, God's law

00:07:02.208 --> 00:07:03.104
Now,

00:07:03.392 --> 00:07:06.752
That obtains always in heaven

00:07:07.072 --> 00:07:10.944
So that's the eternal law that's identical to the divine mind.

00:07:10.976 --> 00:07:18.848
It's the way the realm of the saints and angels is ordered according to love and to justice and peace.

00:07:19.776 --> 00:07:21.088
What are we praying?

00:07:21.376 --> 00:07:25.760
I mean, may that ordering that obtains always in heaven, right?

00:07:27.456 --> 00:07:29.952
Become the ordering of the earth.

00:07:30.816 --> 00:07:34.912
May your kingdom come your will be done

00:07:34.944 --> 00:07:36.320
Here,

00:07:36.448 --> 00:07:37.888
As it is there.

00:07:38.880 --> 00:07:41.920
We're praying for a correspondence.

00:07:42.176 --> 00:07:44.480
Now, Catholics, listen.

00:07:44.384 --> 00:07:47.872
Every single time we come together for the Mass,

00:07:47.936 --> 00:07:51.488
We are begging for and indeed

00:07:51.456 --> 00:07:55.008
Embodying this correspondence.

00:07:55.744 --> 00:07:57.632
When we say, for example,

00:07:58.112 --> 00:07:59.712
at the Holy Holy.

00:07:59.840 --> 00:08:03.360
May our voices blend with theirs.

00:08:03.328 --> 00:08:04.576
We're talking about

00:08:04.352 --> 00:08:06.720
the song of the angels right

00:08:07.328 --> 00:08:12.704
That means the ordering of things in heaven. May our voices hear that

00:08:12.480 --> 00:08:15.680
harmonize with their voices in heaven.

00:08:16.448 --> 00:08:19.040
We're asking for a union.

00:08:19.296 --> 00:08:21.280
of heaven and earth.

00:08:22.176 --> 00:08:28.384
By the way, what are the angels singing? We'll go to the prophet Isaiah, Kaddosh, Kaddosh, Kaddosh.

00:08:28.512 --> 00:08:31.296
Holy holy holy

00:08:31.264 --> 00:08:38.368
Now, see, bring these first parts of the Our Father together. Hallowed be your name. That's the ordering of heaven, you see.

00:08:38.464 --> 00:08:41.376
That's what it's like to be in the kingdom of heaven.

00:08:41.440 --> 00:08:43.296
We're praying that

00:08:43.136 --> 00:08:46.976
That order would become the order of the earth.

00:08:47.712 --> 00:08:55.232
Ah, boy, as I say, the whole of the Christian life, moral life, spiritual life, the life of prayer and liturgy, all of it.

00:08:55.424 --> 00:08:57.888
Is contained in that great petition.

00:08:59.008 --> 00:09:03.232
And then this, I love, because it's so mysterious.

00:09:03.808 --> 00:09:06.816
Give us each day our daily bread.

00:09:07.008 --> 00:09:13.888
The Greek behind this is very intriguing because it's unique really to the Gospels.

00:09:14.112 --> 00:09:15.808
The Greek here is

00:09:15.584 --> 00:09:18.528
2020.

00:09:18.752 --> 00:09:21.824
Our toss means bread in Greek, right?

00:09:22.848 --> 00:09:25.024
What is epi-uzion?

00:09:24.576 --> 00:09:29.088
Well, epi, epi, is like an intensifier. It means on.

00:09:29.248 --> 00:09:34.336
I'm a bishop, for example, and the word episkopos, episkopos,

00:09:34.176 --> 00:09:37.696
Well, scopae means to look, and episcopae means to look.

00:09:37.568 --> 00:09:38.848
Out on.

00:09:38.688 --> 00:09:44.352
All right. So I'm an overseer of the life of the church. That's what Episcopalist means. Well, here we have Ephesians

00:09:44.672 --> 00:09:46.496
Epi-uzion

00:09:46.336 --> 00:09:48.224
Well, "usia" means

00:09:48.160 --> 00:09:49.856
Substance.

00:09:50.464 --> 00:09:54.848
We say, for example, that Jesus is one substance with the Father.

00:09:56.224 --> 00:09:59.104
So "et-vi-us-yos" means

00:10:00.512 --> 00:10:02.656
Super substantial.

