That's it.

00:11:25.184 --> 00:11:28.480
That's what we're asking for in the Our Father.

00:11:28.544 --> 00:11:31.104
"'Give us each day, Lord.'"

00:11:31.648 --> 00:11:35.296
And not just the bread that will keep us alive physically, right?

00:11:35.392 --> 00:11:39.168
But the bread that will keep us alive spiritually.

00:11:39.200 --> 00:11:44.032
Think about that, please, everybody. Next time you pray the Our Father, you come to that line.

00:11:44.032 --> 00:11:45.888
about the daily bread.

00:11:46.336 --> 00:11:47.584
and then of course.

00:11:47.872 --> 00:11:50.432
Forgive us our sins, right?

00:11:50.368 --> 00:11:53.568
As we forgive those who trespass against us.

00:11:54.336 --> 00:11:59.872
Jesus came for all kinds of reasons to teach us and to inspire us and so on, but you could argue

00:12:00.352 --> 00:12:03.008
The main reason he came.

00:12:03.008 --> 00:12:06.016
Was to affect the forgiveness of our sins.

00:12:06.592 --> 00:12:13.952
You know, Fulton Sheen says this so powerfully in his life of Christ, that the temptation of the devil gave him the beginning of his public life.

00:12:13.632 --> 00:12:17.280
We're in the direction of being a Messiah for other purposes.

00:12:17.120 --> 00:12:24.096
You know, to be a bread messiah, to feed the people, to be a wonder worker messiah, to do wonderful things.

00:12:24.032 --> 00:12:26.048
And Jesus resists those.

00:12:26.752 --> 00:12:28.192
No, I have come.

00:12:28.384 --> 00:12:32.384
To die for the forgiveness of sins. That's why he's come.

00:12:33.504 --> 00:12:36.288
And so this prayer, see, is to...

00:12:36.064 --> 00:12:39.552
order us to this great truth about Jesus.

00:12:39.296 --> 00:12:40.704
He's come.

00:12:40.608 --> 00:12:48.672
to forgive our sins. And so we beg to be drawn into the power of that forgiveness. But then, as we forgive,

00:12:50.688 --> 00:12:53.248
Because we're forgiven sinners.

