He says, "Do not subject us to the final test."

00:13:17.792 --> 00:13:24.640
This is a very basic biblical idea. You see it in many places in the Old Testament. The expectation that

00:13:24.576 --> 00:13:27.712
Just before the coming of the Messiah,

00:13:27.968 --> 00:13:29.984
There'd be a time of trial.

00:13:30.720 --> 00:13:32.832
There'd be a time of testing.

00:13:32.800 --> 00:13:42.848
that something awful would happen and people would be tried, see, before the Messiah comes. And so Jesus is tapping into this idea that as we're preparing for

00:13:42.368 --> 00:13:44.960
Erring for the coming of the Messiah, it says,

00:13:44.832 --> 00:13:46.944
We're aware of

00:13:47.168 --> 00:13:49.408
The spiritual struggle

00:13:49.536 --> 00:13:50.848
And see everybody,

00:13:50.656 --> 00:13:54.048
I think this is so basic in the spiritual life.

00:13:54.592 --> 00:14:04.320
It's not just, hey, we're nice people, nice modern people trying to be good-hearted and be nice to our neighbors. I mean, that's fine. But the spiritual life is...

00:14:04.640 --> 00:14:06.656
Is it's a struggle.

00:14:06.976 --> 00:14:11.520
It's a war, as Paul said, against powers and principalities.

00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:14.496
We're up against powers that we can't see.

00:14:15.776 --> 00:14:17.600
And they're not happy

00:14:17.536 --> 00:14:22.944
When we come into deeper communion with Christ, trust me when I tell you this, they're not happy about it.

00:14:23.232 --> 00:14:27.648
What are we praying for here at the end of the prayer is for strength.

00:14:27.488 --> 00:14:29.344
And for courage.

00:14:29.056 --> 00:14:39.040
to face down the spiritual powers that don't want us in union with Christ. I like the spiritual seriousness with which this prayer ends.

00:14:39.456 --> 00:14:40.512
Okay

00:14:40.352 --> 00:14:44.512
So, open your Bibles, take a look at this section of Luke.

00:14:44.736 --> 00:14:48.000
And read through this prayer.

00:14:48.480 --> 00:14:49.792
Slowly.

00:14:50.048 --> 00:14:57.280
And with great spiritual attention. And next time you pray it at Mass, or next time you pray it in your morning prayers or evening prayers,

00:14:57.280 --> 00:15:00.384
Remember these great moves.

